                  <scopecontent id="aspace_39d14f3d0eb81fbfbb99061cc12d8080">
                     <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                     <p>Ayres grew up in Kansas City and graduated from Yale College in 1981. She lived in New Haven from 1975 to 1981. She lived off-campus and considered herself a member of the New Haven lesbian community. Topics covered in the interview include the Gay Alliance at Yale, co-founding of YaLesbians, the Yale Women's Center, the New Haven lesbian community, the New Haven Women's Liberation Center, and student and community interactions. Also discussed are the issues that were relevant to Ayres and her cohort including feminism, radical lesbian feminism, racism, classism, and social justice and peace work.</p>
                  </scopecontent>
                  <userestrict id="aspace_4326e4700b4a999ec5214a6c5333cc5b">
                     <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
                     <p>Permission required from the interviewee to cite or quote until January 1, 2037.</p>
                  </userestrict>
